White County was named in honour of the Surveyor and Diarist George Boyle White (1802-1876).

White County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located to the south of the Namoi River along both sides of Bohena Creek, with Narrabri at the northern end. It includes most of the Pilliga Nature Reserve.
